    "He met the poet Rainer Maria Rilke (1875-1926) in 1915.": [],
    "He expanded his <em>Der nackte Mensch</em> into a larger book on art sociology, <em>Die Kunst und die Gesellschaft</em>, 1916.": [],
    "During his military service in World War I, he was stationed in Brussels from 1916-17.": [],
    "There he edited the German-language journal <em>Der Belfried</em> and contributed to the <em>Frankfurter Zeitung</em> and the art journal <em>Die Kunstblatt</em> edited by <a href=\"/westheimp\">Paul Westheim</a>.": [],
    "In Brussels he met his future wife, Margot Kohn Lipper (1890-1997), widow of a fallen German soldier.": [
