    "Hausenstein wrote an open letter to Thomas Mann (1875-1955), published in the <em>S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung</em> in December 1945, refuting Mann's claim that all literature published in Germany during the Third Reich was worthless, citing many examples, including art-historical literature.": [
